- Let's go!

36
00:06:44,190 --> 00:06:44,870
Daji.

37
00:06:51,630 --> 00:06:53,140
It's been a while, Mr. Lin.

38
00:06:54,220 --> 00:06:55,020
It has.

39
00:06:57,190 --> 00:06:58,550
I want to make Such A Good Love

40
00:06:58,990 --> 00:07:00,340
into a film.

41
00:07:00,670 --> 00:07:01,820
Directed by me.

42
00:07:02,460 --> 00:07:04,110
I heard you and Zhou Shui

43
00:07:04,110 --> 00:07:05,950
were shooting a film for Ruidi.

44
00:07:06,140 --> 00:07:07,460
Why are you back on your own?

45
00:07:08,430 --> 00:07:09,870
I told you before...

46
00:07:09,870 --> 00:07:10,750
It's fine.

47
00:07:11,430 --> 00:07:12,670
We broke up.

48
00:07:12,990 --> 00:07:14,460
I'm not working on that film anymore.

49
00:07:14,750 --> 00:07:15,900
That's a shame.

50
00:07:17,550 --> 00:07:19,220
Let's get back to Such A Good Love then.

51
00:07:20,110 --> 00:07:21,140
I'll be upfront.

52
00:07:21,670 --> 00:07:22,820
I've pitched it to a bunch

53
00:07:22,990 --> 00:07:24,460
of companies the past two months.

54
00:07:25,020 --> 00:07:26,380
No luck.

55
00:07:27,510 --> 00:07:29,380
Shendu is my last shot.

56
00:07:30,260 --> 00:07:31,460
So just give it to me straight.

57
00:07:32,260 --> 00:07:33,190
Yes or no.

58
00:07:33,700 --> 00:07:35,820
Don't worry. We'll give this film

59
00:07:35,820 --> 00:07:37,460
our full support.

60
00:07:37,460 --> 00:07:38,020
Su.

61
00:07:38,340 --> 00:07:39,550
I read the script

62
00:07:39,550 --> 00:07:40,870
a long time ago.

63
00:07:40,870 --> 00:07:41,780
And honestly,

64
00:07:41,780 --> 00:07:44,380
it's one of the best I've ever seen.

65
00:07:44,900 --> 00:07:45,700
Daji.

66
00:07:45,820 --> 00:07:47,630
Your script is more
on the artistic side.

67
00:07:47,820 --> 00:07:49,260
There's no big hook.

68
00:07:49,260 --> 00:07:50,870
Did you even read the script carefully?

69
00:07:50,870 --> 00:07:52,430
It's realistic.

70
00:07:52,430 --> 00:07:54,920
But it won't be popular.
No way to bring in A-list talent.

71
00:07:55,140 --> 00:07:55,700
And

72
00:07:55,700 --> 00:07:57,510
the story's set ten years ago, right?

73
00:07:57,900 --> 00:07:58,990
That's dated.

74
00:07:59,380 --> 00:08:01,260
Nostalgia is trendy right now though.

75
00:08:01,460 --> 00:08:03,110
Look at Eternal Moment, Fleet of Time,

76
00:08:03,110 --> 00:08:03,870
I Belonged to You.

77
00:08:03,870 --> 00:08:04,110
All...

78
00:08:04,110 --> 00:08:06,310
What I want for Shendu isn't nostalgia.

79
00:08:06,310 --> 00:08:08,020
I want now, urban, fresh.

80
00:08:08,220 --> 00:08:09,070
Anyway,

81
00:08:09,220 --> 00:08:11,260
go revise the script.

82
00:08:11,340 --> 00:08:12,380
She's the director.

83
00:08:12,390 --> 00:08:13,020
Daji, it's okay.

84
00:08:13,020 --> 00:08:14,220
I'll help you rewrite it.

85
00:08:14,220 --> 00:08:15,020
- You...
- Right now...

86
00:08:15,020 --> 00:08:15,630
Sorry.

87
00:08:17,640 --> 00:08:19,460
I'm not changing
a single word of this script.

88
00:08:20,190 --> 00:08:22,220
And I want full control over the edit.

89
00:08:25,140 --> 00:08:27,430
With all these demands,
it's not going to work.

90
00:08:28,110 --> 00:08:30,780
If you want to direct,
you need to learn to compromise.

91
00:08:31,340 --> 00:08:32,700
I'm not doing this just to direct.

92
00:08:34,270 --> 00:08:36,030
I want this movie to be made.

93
00:08:36,910 --> 00:08:38,790
And I want to make it
without compromise.

94
00:08:40,390 --> 00:08:42,550
If you won't compromise,
you won't get investment.

95
00:08:42,820 --> 00:08:44,820
And without money,
how are you going to shoot it?

96
00:08:45,550 --> 00:08:46,820
Then I'll fund it myself.

97
00:08:49,310 --> 00:08:50,390
Surely you know

98
00:08:50,550 --> 00:08:52,030
how expensive making a movie is.

99
00:08:52,950 --> 00:08:54,030
It's not pocket change.

100
00:08:54,500 --> 00:08:55,310
I know.

101
00:08:56,750 --> 00:08:57,910
If I can't afford a feature,

102
00:08:57,910 --> 00:08:59,190
I'll make a short.

103
00:08:59,740 --> 00:09:02,620
But Such A Good Love
has to be done my way.

104
00:09:04,740 --> 00:09:06,580
Well, best of luck then.

105
00:09:15,620 --> 00:09:16,550
Daji! Wait!

106
00:09:19,220 --> 00:09:20,460
Anything else, Mr. Lin?

107
00:09:21,240 --> 00:09:22,820
What happened between you and Zhou Shui?

108
00:09:23,700 --> 00:09:24,700
What do you mean?

109
00:09:25,670 --> 00:09:27,150
We broke up.

110
00:09:28,140 --> 00:09:29,460
Haven't you ever broken up before?

111
00:09:31,430 --> 00:09:32,220
He's been

112
00:09:32,340 --> 00:09:34,070
going crazy looking for you.

113
00:09:34,310 --> 00:09:35,790
He's not doing well at all.

114
00:09:36,500 --> 00:09:37,190
Once,

115
00:09:37,190 --> 00:09:38,150
he called me at 5 AM

116
00:09:38,150 --> 00:09:39,580
asking where you were.

117
00:09:39,580 --> 00:09:41,620
He's asked me,
asked Xue Cheng, asked Xiaomao.

118
00:09:41,700 --> 00:09:42,950
He's looking for you every day.

119
00:09:43,790 --> 00:09:45,670
Did you tell him
I was coming here today?

120
00:09:45,950 --> 00:09:47,430
Didn't you ask me not to?

121
00:09:47,700 --> 00:09:48,670
But I really think

122
00:09:48,670 --> 00:09:50,700
you should tell him about the movie.

123
00:09:51,270 --> 00:09:52,580
He could help you.

124
00:09:53,950 --> 00:09:54,910
I don't want his help.

125
00:09:56,340 --> 00:09:57,150
I can

126
00:09:57,950 --> 00:09:59,190
make a movie on my own.

